<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="38" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/924</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moser</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-10T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            10, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Authorization to send <persName corresp="#p_DLCWS1">Drysdale</persName> as requested through Legation is granted.
                                Telegraph approximate expense. Naval attaché Peking suggests
                                advisability of sending to assist <persName corresp="#p_DLCWS1">Drysdale</persName> a Serbian Colonel
                                    <persName>Speskov</persName> now available Peking, who has
                                offered services, is thoroughly familiar with situation and speaks
                                necessary languages. Advise Minister Peking what you recommend.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>